-- Two Secret Service Agents Said to Resign in Prostitute Case
-- B y   J e f f   B l i s s
-- 2012-04-18T21:52:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-18/two-secret-service-agents-said-to-resign-in-prostitute-case.html
Two Secret Service agents have
resigned and a third is retiring after allegations that their
team associated with prostitutes in advance of President Barack
Obama's visit to  Colombia  for a summit, said a congressional aide.  The departures are the first from the allegations that were
made as the Summit of the Americas was beginning last week in
Cartagena.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jeff Bliss in Washington at 
 jbliss@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
